Reasoning: 
1. cs.SD (Sound): The paper is about generating orchestral music in real-time, which involves sound processing and manipulation. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a machine learning model (cRBM) for learning the regularities between piano scores and their orchestrations, which falls under the domain of AI. 
3. cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper discusses the implementation of the proposed model (LOP) for real-time orchestration of a MIDI keyboard input, which involves signal processing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper introduces an evaluation framework for orchestral generation based on a prediction task, which can be seen as a network of information flow. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a machine learning model (cRBM) for learning the regularities between piano scores and their orchestrations, which falls under the domain of machine learning.
